erbyshire placename probably derives from Old English <i>winn</i> ‘pasture, meadow’ + <i>feld</i> ‘open country’. The Bedfordshire placename may derive from Old English <i>wince</i> ‘nook, corner’ + <i>feld</i>. The Suffolk placename may derive from the Old English personal name <i>Wiga</i> + the Old English groupname suffix <i>-ingas</i> (genitive <i>-inga-</i>) or Old English <i>wīg</i> ‘idol’ + <i>feld</i>. The Wiltshire placename derives from the Old English personal name <i>Wina</i> + Old English <i>feld</i>."]}]},{"name":"Eleanor","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ellenor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor  , the result of blending with   Ellen ."]},{"name":"Elenor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]},{"name":"Elinor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Eleanor Wingfield was born in 1358. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Sir William Hoo. She died after 1415."},"et":{"1358–after 1415":"1358–pärast 1415","1342–1410":"1342–1410","1367–Male":"1367–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1358–1415":"1358–1415","1415":"1415","1358":"1358","after 1415":"pärast 1415","November 1410":"november 1410","1367":"1367","1410":"1410","1342":"1342","about 1367":"umbes 1367","Mulbarton, Norfolk, England":"Mulbarton, Norfolk, England","Luton Hoo, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Luton Hoo, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1358–after 1415":"1358–1415 jälkeen","1342–1410":"1342–1410","1367–Male":"1367–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1358–1415":"1358–1415","1415":"1415","1358":"1358","after 1415":"1415 jälkeen","November 1410":"marraskuu 1410","1367":"1367","1410":"1410","1342":"1342","about 1367":"noin 1367","Mulbarton, Norfolk, England":"Mulbarton, Norfolk, England","Luton Hoo, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Luton Hoo, Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1358–after 1415":"1358–après 1415","1342–1410":"1342–1410","1367–Male":"1367–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1358–1415":"1358–1415","1415":"1415","1358":"1358","after 1415":"après 1415","November 1410":"novembre 1410","1367":"1367","1410":"1410","1342":"1342","about 1367":"environ 1367","Mulbarton, Norfolk, England":"Mulbarton, Norfolk, Angleterre","Luton Hoo, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Luton Hoo, Bedfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Eleanor Wingfield est née en 1358. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille avec Sir William Hoo. Elle est décédée après 1415."},"de":{"1358–after 1415":"1358–nach 1415","1342–1410":"1342–1410","1367–Male":"1367–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1358–1415":"1358–1415","1415":"1415","1358":"1358","after 1415":"nach 1415","November 1410":"November 1410","1367":"1367","1410":"1410","1342":"1342","about 1367":"um 1367","Mulbarton, Norfolk, England":"Mulbarton, Norfolk, England","Luton Hoo, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Luton H